# Backend Code Review Checklist
# Node.js + Express + Discord Webhooks

## Security
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials/API keys (use .env)
- [ ] All user input validated and sanitized
- [ ] SQL injection prevention (if using DB)
- [ ] CORS configured correctly
- [ ] Helmet security headers enabled
- [ ] Rate limiting configured (express-rate-limit)
- [ ] Environment variables validated on startup
- [ ] Secrets never logged or exposed

## API Design
- [ ] RESTful conventions followed
- [ ] Proper HTTP status codes used
- [ ] Consistent error response format
- [ ] Request validation middleware
- [ ] Authentication/authorization checks
- [ ] API versioning considered
- [ ] Request logging (morgan) configured

## Performance
- [ ] Database queries optimized (if applicable)
- [ ] Async/await used properly
- [ ] No blocking operations in request handlers
- [ ] Appropriate timeout configurations
- [ ] Memory leaks prevented

## Code Quality
- [ ] No console.logs (use proper logging)
- [ ] Error handling middleware implemented
- [ ] Try/catch blocks for async operations
- [ ] Functions under 50 lines
- [ ] Clear variable/function names
- [ ] Environment configs separated from code
- [ ] Comments only where needed

## Error Handling
- [ ] Global error handler middleware
- [ ] Async errors caught properly
- [ ] Meaningful error messages
- [ ] Error logging implemented
- [ ] Graceful shutdown on critical errors

## Discord Integration
- [ ] Webhook URLs stored securely
- [ ] Payload formatting validated (Discord embed format)
- [ ] Retry logic for failed webhooks
- [ ] Rate limiting for Discord API (5 requests/2 seconds)
- [ ] Error handling for failed notifications
- [ ] Embed limits respected (6000 chars total, 256 title, 4096 description)

## Environment & Config
- [ ] .env.example up to date
- [ ] All required env vars documented
- [ ] Environment validation on startup
- [ ] Proper NODE_ENV handling
- [ ] Port configuration flexible

## Before Commit
- [ ] Code runs locally without errors
- [ ] All routes tested manually/automatically
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs
- [ ] Dependencies up to date (npm audit)
- [ ] Reviewed changes in git diff
- [ ] README updated if needed
